
Since you just want a simple frontend-only dummy web app (no backend, no Python) — we can do that super easily with just React (the one already running on your PC).

Let’s make a cute, simple Fake News Detector Demo — it won’t use any ML or backend, but will simulate results for project presentation.


---

⚙️ Step-by-Step Setup

🪄 Step 1 — Open your frontend app in VS Code

Make sure your project structure looks like:

frontend/
 └── src/
     └── App.js


---

🪄 Step 2 — Replace the code in App.js

Open src/App.js, delete everything, and paste this 👇

import React, { useState } from "react";
import "./App.css";

function App() {
  const [news, setNews] = useState("");
  const [result, setResult] = useState("");

  const handleCheck = () => {
    if (!news.trim()) {
      alert("Please enter some news text!");
      return;
    }

    // 🔹 Dummy logic: randomly decide fake or real
    const random = Math.random() < 0.5 ? "Fake News 🚨" : "True News ✅";
    setResult(random);
  };

  return (
    <div className="container">
      <h1>📰 Fake News Detection Demo</h1>
      <textarea
        placeholder="Enter news headline or text..."
        value={news}
        onChange={(e) => setNews(e.target.value)}
      />
      <button onClick={handleCheck}>Check News</button>
      {result && (
        <div className={`result ${result.includes("Fake") ? "fake" : "true"}`}>
          {result}
        </div>
      )}
    </div>
  );
}

export default App;


---

🪄 Step 3 — Add simple CSS for beauty

Open (or create) the file:
📄 src/App.css

Paste this:

.container {
  text-align: center;
  margin-top: 60px;
  font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
}

h1 {
  color: #2c3e50;
  margin-bottom: 30px;
}

textarea {
  width: 70%;
  height: 120px;
  padding: 10px;
  font-size: 16px;
  border: 2px solid #ccc;
  border-radius: 10px;
  outline: none;
  resize: none;
}

button {
  margin-top: 15px;
  padding: 10px 30px;
  background-color: #3498db;
  color: white;
  border: none;
  border-radius: 8px;
  cursor: pointer;
  font-size: 16px;
}

button:hover {
  background-color: #2980b9;
}

.result {
  margin-top: 25px;
  font-size: 22px;
  font-weight: bold;
  padding: 15px;
  border-radius: 10px;
  width: fit-content;
  margin-left: auto;
  margin-right: auto;
}

.result.fake {
  color: white;
  background-color: #e74c3c;
}

.result.true {
  color: white;
  background-color: #27ae60;
}


---

🪄 Step 4 — Run your app

In your terminal:

npm start

Your browser will open at http://localhost:3000
Now you’ll see:

📰 Fake News Detection Demo
A textbox → “Check News” button → and random result like ✅ True News or 🚨 Fake News.


---

✅ What You Have Now

✔️ 100% Frontend-only
✔️ No backend, no Python
✔️ Works offline
✔️ Looks clean and ready for project demo
✔️ You can say it’s a “simulation model for fake news detection”


